name: COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania, Appellant, v. Chris A. FREY, Appellee

judges: Before FLAHERTY, C.J., and ZAPPALA, CAPPY, CASTILLE, NIGRO, NEWMAN and SAYLOR, JJ.
parties: COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania, Appellant, v. Chris A. FREY, Appellee.

opinions.text:
ORDER
PER CURIAM.
Based upon our disposition in Commonwealth v. Williams, 557 Pa. 285, 733 A.2d 593 (1999), we affirm the Order of the Centre County Court of Common Pleas dated March 15, 1999. Furthermore, we remand the matter to the common pleas court for disposition of any remaining issues.
Jurisdiction is relinquished.
opinions.author: PER CURIAM.

attorneys: J. Karen Arnold, Asst. Dist. Atty., District Attorney’s Office, for Com.
Ronald McGlaughlin, State College, for Chris A. Frey.
